node.title: Victoria records 1,247 new local COVID-19 cases and nine deaths
node.alt: People seated in chairs waiting for a COVID vaccine
node.description: There are now 17,674 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 335 people have died in the state during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,247\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and nine\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 17,674\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 335\u00a0people have died in the state during the current Delta outbreak.", "Today's figures come after two days of case counts that dipped below the 1,000 mark \u2014 Thursdays typically have\u00a0the highest numbers of new cases reported.\u00a0", "There are now 660\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 114\u00a0are in intensive care and 78\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The new cases were detected from 50,180\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 16,209\u00a0doses of vaccine given at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
How to take a rapid antigen test
